The People of the State of New York, Respondent, v. George Budner, Appellant. Submitted April 27, 1964; decided April 30, 1964. *724George Budner, pro se, for motions.

No one opposed.

Motions dismissed. Upon the court’s own motion, appeal dismissed for the reason that sentence has not yet been imposed and no appeal will lie (Code Crim. Pro., § 519).
